                   Scoop Du Jour   
                  
                    Mon Nov 28 07:51am EST 
                     Dalembert wants to sign with Heat  
                    By       Mark J. Miller  /  Scoop Du Jour   
                   
                  
                  
                   
                        The  Miami Heat  is about to start loading up again for its attempt at an NBA championship with  LeBron James  (notes) ,  Dwyane Wade  (notes) , and  Chris Bosh  (notes)  onboard. The team's main need is at center and it  already has a big talented fella knocking at the door  who would like to suit up. FOX Sports has it that 6-11  Samuel Dalembert  (notes)  would like to sign on with the Heat this offseason. "Miami is where more than 50 of his relatives live and is about one hour south of his home in Boca Raton," the site notes.   Dalembert made $13.43 million last season with the  Sacramento Kings , but might have to find a way to survive on only a $5 million midlevel contract, FOX reports, due to Miami's already overstuffed payroll.   "I'm keeping all my options open, but Miami could be a good fit for me," Dalembert said, according to FOX. "If you look at the playoffs with Dallas, you saw what (Mavericks center)  Tyson Chandler  (notes)  did. He was basically a key ingredient for them to win a championship. And Miami didn't have somebody like that. Somebody able to stop (foes from) getting second shots and somebody able to rebound and finish. I could fill that role and be an asset for that team."  The 30-year-old Dalembert averaged 8.1 points, 8.2 rebounds, and 1.45 blocks last season for the Kings.  Let the rumors come to you. Follow Scoop du Jour on  Twitter  or  Facebook . 
                    Source:  FOX Sports  
                   
                  
                 
               
                              
                
                  
                    
