                   Scoop Du Jour   
                  
                    Mon Nov 28 07:37am EST 
                     Texans not calling on Favre  
                    By       Mark J. Miller  /  Scoop Du Jour   
                   
                  
                  
                   
                        The  Houston Texans  have lost starting quarterbacks  Matt Schaub  (notes)  and  Matt Leinart  (notes)  for the season in the past several weeks, but that doesn't mean the team is going to make a desperation call. Texans GM Rick Smith told SI.com that the team  isn't going to call  on  Brett Favre  (notes) , who has come out of retirement on more than one occasion, to come back and play hero for his team.   Plus, SI has it that Favre hasn't even thrown a football since early November so it wouldn't be easy to get the 42-year-old back into shape fast enough to be effective as the season heads into the stretch run.  The Texans currently lead the AFC South by two games with an 8-3 record after a 20-13 win over the  Jacksonville Jaguars  that found rookie  T.J. Yates  (notes)  calling the shots by game's end. Yates went 8-for-15 for 70 yards. He also attempted to run the ball four times, but lost three yards in the process.  Don't forget to follow Scoop du Jour on  Twitter  or  Facebook . 
                    Source:  SI.com  
                   
                  
                 
               
                              
                
                  
                    
