                   Scoop Du Jour   
                  
                    Mon Nov 28 07:00am EST 
                     Crawford headed to Knicks or Nets?  
                    By       Mark J. Miller  /  Scoop Du Jour   
                   
                  
                  
                   
                        Now that the new NBA collective bargaining agreement is thisclose to being a done deal, free-agent signing rumors are starting to suddenly bubble up. No player can sign with a new team till Dec. 9.   The word from the New York Daily News is that one of those free agents, veteran shooting guard  Jamal Crawford  (notes) , is likely to sign with a former employer, the  New York Knicks , or the  New Jersey Nets , if the  Atlanta Hawks  don't make a good enough effort to re-sign him.  The 30-year-old Crawford, who is repped by New Jersey-based Andy Miller at ASM Sports,  would like to return to the New York area , a source tells the paper.  Crawford, who won the NBA Sixth Man of the Year award in 2010, last played for the Knicks back in the 2008-09 season before being traded to the  Golden State Warriors . He's spent the last two seasons with the Hawks, where he averaged 14.2 points, 3.2 assists, and 1.7 rebounds per game last year.   Let the rumors come to you. Follow Scoop du Jour on  Twitter  or  Facebook . 
                    Source:  New York Daily News  
                   
                  
                 
               
                              
                
                  
                    
