                   Scoop Du Jour   
                  
                    Mon Nov 28 06:39am EST 
                     Astros toss GM Wade  
                    By       Mark J. Miller  /  Scoop Du Jour   
                   
                  
                  
                   
                        The month before Ed Wade was hired by the  Houston Astros  to be the general manager back in 2007, he went parachuting in New Jersey and found himself  accidentally dangling from a tree . He must have had a similar feeling in recent days as his future with the team seemed tenuous as best. FOX Sports reported Sunday that the team  would be canning Wade on Monday.  The  team then  confirmed that report  in a press release, according to MLBTradeRumors.com.   The 55-year-old Wade started his baseball career back in 1977 as a public-relations intern with the  Philadelphia Phillies  before eventually serving as that team's general manager from 1998 to 2005. In Philly, Wade was responsible for drafting  Chase Utley  (notes) ,  Ryan Howard  (notes) , and  Cole Hamels  (notes)  as well as hiring manager Charlie Manuel. In Houston, many of his biggest trades have been with the Phillies, sending  Brad Lidge  (notes) ,  Roy Oswalt  (notes) , and  Hunter Pence  (notes)  to his former employer.  Let the rumors come to you. Follow Scoop du Jour on    Twitter  or  Facebook . 
                    Source:  FOX Sports  WPVI  
                   
                  
                 
               
                              
                
                  
                    
