                   Scoop Du Jour   
                  
                    Mon Nov 28 06:16am EST 
                     Next Red Sox manager: Lamont and Valentine  
                    By       Mark J. Miller  /  Scoop Du Jour   
                   
                  
                  
                   
                        Bobby Valentine and Gene Lamont are said to the be  the last men standing  in the search for a new manager for the  Boston Red Sox , according to ESPN, but neither had received an offer as of Sunday night.  Detroit Tigers  third-base coach Lamont, who has managed the  Pittsburgh Pirates  and  Oakland Athletics , met with Red Sox majority owner John Henry on Tuesday in Boca Raton, Florida, the site notes, "where Henry maintains a home" and then flew up to New York the next day to talk with Red Sox chairman Tom Werner.  "I've talked to people,'' the soon-to-be 65-year-old Lamont said, ESPN reports, "but I don't know what their time frame is now.''  The 61-year-old Valentine hasn't managed in the majors since 2002. His best season came in 2000 when he took the  New York Mets  to the World Series. He also won the Japan Series in 2005 with the Chiba Lotte Marines before returning to the States in 2009 to become an analyst with ESPN.  Let the rumors come to you. Follow Scoop du Jour on  Twitter  or  Facebook . 
                    Source:  ESPN  
                   
                  
                 
               
                              
                
                  
                    
