                   Scoop Du Jour   
                  
                    Mon Nov 28 05:58am EST 
                     C.J. Wilson visiting Marlins  
                    By       Mark J. Miller  /  Scoop Du Jour   
                   
                  
                  
                   
                        The rebranding Miami Marlins have been the most publicly aggressive team this offseason with offers being made to free agents  Albert Pujols  (notes) ,  Jose Reyes  (notes) , and  Mark Buehrle  (notes) . Now the offseason's  top starting pitcher is coming to town . The South Florida Sun Sentinel has it that lefty  C.J. Wilson  (notes)  will visit with the Marlins Monday.  The  Los Angeles Angels  are also after the 31-year-old Wilson and the  Texas Rangers  would like to re-sign the fella who went 16-7 with a 2.94 ERA and 206 strikeouts last season to help the team to its second consecutive visit to the World Series.  Don't forget to follow Scoop du Jour on  Twitter  or  Facebook . 
                    Source:  South Florida Sun Sentinel  
                   
                  
                 
               
                              
                
                  
                    
