                   Scoop Du Jour   
                  
                    Mon Nov 28 05:54am EST 
                     Tigers interested in Aramis Ramirez and Mark Buehrle?  
                    By       Mark J. Miller  /  Scoop Du Jour   
                   
                  
                  
                   
                        Free agent third baseman  Aramis Ramirez  (notes)  has been with the  Chicago Cubs  since 2003 but the team's new management doesn't seen to expect him to return to the Windy City. Now it looks like another team is interested in bringing the 33-year-old three-time All-Star back to the Midwest. SI.com reports that the  Detroit Tigers  are  inquiring about Ramirez , who hit .306 with 26 homers and 35 doubles last season.  The Tigers are also  interested in making a run  at snagging 32-year-old free agent pitcher  Mark Buehrle  (notes) , the Detroit News reports, but know they have stiff competition for the guy who has gone 161-119 in his career with a 3.83 ERA.  Follow Scoop du Jour on  Twitter  or  Facebook . 
                    Source:  SI.com  Detroit News  
                   
                  
                 
               
                              
                
                  
                    
