                   Scoop Du Jour   
                  
                    Mon Nov 28 05:48am EST 
                     Head injury sidelines Seahawks WR Rice  
                    By       Mark J. Miller  /  Scoop Du Jour   
                   
                  
                  
                   
                        The  Seattle Seahawks ' season took a major hit Sunday when the team lost a 10-point lead with 12 minutes to play and got buried by the  Washington Redskins  23-17, leaving the 'Hawks at 4-7 on the year. During the battle, wide receiver  Sidney Rice  (notes)  went down in the third quarter with a head injury after " he hit his head on the turf  trying to make a diving catch across the middle," according to the Associated Press.  The 25-year-old former Pro Bowler, who was drafted in 2007's second round, went without a catch the whole night. He has 484 yards receiving this season along with two touchdown catches.  Don't forget to follow Scoop du Jour on  Twitter  or  Facebook . 
                    Source:  Associated Press  
                   
                  
                 
               
                              
                
                  
                    
