                   Scoop Du Jour   
                  
                    Mon Nov 28 05:44am EST 
                     Steelers' Polamalu has concussion?  
                    By       Mark J. Miller  /  Scoop Du Jour   
                   
                  
                  
                   
                        On the first drive of the  Pittsburgh Steelers ' 13-9 win over the  Kansas City Chiefs , strong safety  Troy Polamalu  (notes)  went down with  a possible concussion , according to the Pittsburgh Post-Gazette. The 30-year-old Polamalu, the 2010 defensive player of the year and a six-time Pro Bowler, was taken down by 290-pound tackle Chris Maneri on the play, the paper reports, and then "wobbled off the field and sat on the bench under a coat."  The 207-pound Polamalu has 64 tackles and one sack this season.  Find out before your friends. Follow Scoop du Jour on  Twitter  or  Facebook . 
                    Source:  Pittsburgh Post-Gazette  
                   
                  
                 
               
                              
                
                  
                    
